sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant APIServer as API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Redis as Redis<br/>6379/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Processor as Batch Processor
    participant InfGW as Inference Gateway<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant GC as Garbage Collector

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Batch Job Submission
        Client->>APIServer: POST /v1/files (multipart/form-data)<br/>Auth: X-MaaS-Username header
        APIServer->>S3: Upload input file<br/>TLS 1.2+ / AWS credentials
        APIServer->>PG: Store file metadata<br/>TLS (optional) / conn string
        APIServer-->>Client: File ID

        Client->>APIServer: POST /v1/batches<br/>Auth: X-MaaS-Username header
        APIServer->>PG: Store batch metadata<br/>TLS (optional) / conn string
        APIServer->>Redis: Enqueue to priority queue (sorted set)<br/>SLO-based score
        APIServer-->>Client: Batch ID + status: validating
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Processor,S3: Flow 2: Batch Job Processing
        Processor->>Redis: Dequeue job (ZPOPMIN)<br/>poll_interval: 5s
        Processor->>PG: Read batch metadata
        Processor->>S3: Download input file<br/>TLS 1.2+ / AWS credentials
        Note over Processor: Parse JSONL, group by model,<br/>sort by FNV-32a hash,<br/>create binary plan (16-byte entries)
        loop For each request in plan (concurrency: 100 global, 10 per-model)
            Processor->>InfGW: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer token<br/>Headers: x-slo-ttft-ms, x-gateway-inference-objective
            InfGW-->>Processor: Inference response
        end
        Processor->>S3: Upload output file<br/>TLS 1.2+ / AWS credentials
        Processor->>S3: Upload error file (if any)
        Processor->>PG: Update batch status: completed
        Processor->>Redis: Update progress cache (TTL: 24h)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 230)
        Note over Client,Redis: Flow 3: Batch Job Cancellation
        Client->>APIServer: POST /v1/batches/{id}/cancel<br/>Auth: X-MaaS-Username header
        APIServer->>PG: Update status: cancelling
        APIServer->>Redis: Publish cancel event (LPUSH)
        APIServer-->>Client: status: cancelling
        Redis-->>Processor: Cancel event received (BRPOP)
        Processor->>S3: Upload partial results
        Processor->>PG: Update status: cancelled
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over GC,S3: Flow 4: Garbage Collection (every 30m)
        GC->>PG: Query expired batches/files
        GC->>S3: Delete expired file content
        GC->>PG: Delete expired metadata
    end
